CHOLERA, DIARRHEA & DYSENTERY UPDATE (21): ASIA (YEMEN)
*******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 24 May 2018
Source: WHO/EMRO, Electronic Disease Early Warning System (eDEWS) [edited]
http://www.emro.who.int/images/stories/yemen/week_20.pdf?ua=1


Yemen: Cholera Response Weekly Epidemiological Bulletin: W20 2018 (14-20 May 2018)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Highlights
----------
Cumulative figures
-The cumulative total from 27 Apr 2017 to 20 May 2018 is 1 100 720 suspected cholera cases and 2291 associated deaths, (CFR 0.21 percent), 1119 have been confirmed by culture.
- The total proportion of severe cases among the suspected cases is 15.3 percent.
- The national attack rate is 392.8 per 10 000. The 5 governorates with the highest cumulative attack rates per 10 000 remain Amran (916), Al Mahwit (891), Al Dhale'e (639), Dhamar (535), Sana'a (535).
- Children under 5 years old represent 28.8 percent of total suspected cases.
- In total, 53220 rapid diagnostic tests (RDT).
- 3988 cultures have been performed which represents 26 percent coverage.
- The last positive culture was on 4 May 2018 in Al Hali district in Al Hudeideh governorate.
- Since 1 Jan 2018 the districts with highest cumulative suspected cases are Al Hali (5154), Radman Al Awad (2019), Al Sabaeen (1940), Maqbanah (1912) , Al Mighlaf (1834).
- 155 districts are still reporting suspected cholera cases since last 3 weeks.
- 150 districts (out of 305 affected districts) did not report any suspected cases for the last 3 consecutive weeks.

Governorate and District level
- At governorate level, the trend from W17 -W19 decrease or was stable in all governorates, except Sana'a (+42 percent), Al Hudeideh (+12 percent), Raymeh (+19 percent), Ibb (+21 percent), Taizz (+23 percent).

Trends
- The weekly proportion of severe cases has significantly decreased (now 18 percent).

Week 20 2018 [14-20 May 2018]
- 1874 suspected cases and 2 associated deaths were reported
- The districts reporting the highest number of cases are Amran (87), Al Hali (81), Al Mighlaf (74), Mukayras (65)
- 18 percent are severe cases
- 1872 RDTs were performed, 244 were positive
- no culture results received this week

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

