Over the past 5 weeks of reporting, it appears that there have been 11213 additional cases. Although the numbers had decreased, the new period increased averaging about 320 cases PER DAY. The low case fatality rate might suggest that some of the diarrhea may be non-cholera. Although the daily rate had dropped significantly, this many new diarrhea cases per day remains substantial. There has been a slowing of cases during the 3-month period of January-March 2017 as well. The daily rate seems to be moving upwards a bit.

